  <thing id="spSGExsngn" name="Exsanguination" description="This spell causes blood to start pouring out of the target’s orifices, causing it to suffer bleed damage equal to the caster’s level. A successful Fortitude save reduces the bleed damage by half. \n\nThe blood loss is devastating – unlike normal bleed damage, it’s not immediately stopped by any application of healing. Each time the target receives magic healing, the source of that healing makes a caster level check (DC 10 + caster level of the exsanguination), ending the bleed effect on a successful check. A succesful Heal check reduces the bleed rate by 1 with a DC 15 skill check. Multiple successful Heal checks are cumulative. \n\nAny allies of the bleeding victim who can see him must make a Will save at the save DC of the exsanguination spell, or be sickened for one round. \n\nThe bleed effect of multiple exsanguination spells do not stack. The spell does not work on creatures without blood, such as most oozes, constructs, and undead." compset="Spell">
